Final Conclusion
Overall, after combining all of the “Bestness” scores from all three of our datasets, the best neighborhood to live in Pittsburgh is Highland park, with a average combined bestness score of .757.
This score comes from a saftey score of .817 and a bestness score of .454 and a housing economy score of 1.
In second place in Brookline which was had a score of .7 so this was a pretty significant win by Highland park.
Highland Park was the best in housing economy so we suspected it to be one of the top neighborhoods.
Overall we collected data, sorted and calculate our bestness scores then combined them to come to the colclution that Highland park in the best neighborhood to live in pittsburgh.
